caption: Ninja Sushi went from a great place to a place that has inferior quality and sub-par sushi masters. For a year now, it has been sometimes good, sometimes not. As I order mostly rolls, this means sometimes too much rice and other times the rice doesn't even cover the seaweed. Then, the fish is very little. Not even a sliver, and the veggies almost non-existent. The placing in the tray with skimpy sushi allows movement and so my sushi often loses form. And, today the soy sauce was bad. Goodbye Ninja sushi! You just lost a long-time, loyal, and free spending customer. There are too many other places to be bothered and disappointed with you.

**Review is from January 10, 2020-- not sure why Google has this  posted in 2021?? Just as the business business has replied that they are not opened, I am no longer living New York. With such a detailed review, you'd expect the "owner" to exercise common sense that this interaction did not happen post-covid,?? Just a thought.  Original review from 01/10/2020:  Horrible customer service. They dont take reservations on "weekends." Friday night is also a weekend, so you've been warned. I called the day before and was told to call again  1hr before my reservation. I called 1hr before my reservation and was told they do not take reservations at this time because the time I am booking will have customers walk in, so come in a bit before the time you want to reserve to book the tables (we are planning for a party of 10). I went in 45mins before the time I want to book and the staff had an internal discussion, in Mandarin, saying that my party is too large and other tables will be gone for new customers if we book it, also mentioned that my party is more than 15 people, which is not.  I spoke to them in English, so maybe they thought I didnt understand Chinese. Well, I do understand them and I also understand that this place is not very accommodating.

TO GO AYCE in Brooklyn. There are plenty of competition in the area however hands down, would choose Ninja anyday. Appetizer: Huge selection of salad like kani, seaweed, green, avocado, spicy seafood, salmon skin. Important note: the avocado was fresh and ripe, perfectly riped, NOT brown at all. A lot of variety of carbohydrates and filling to choose from: udon, soba, fried rice, stir fry. Teriyaki is highly recommended. Teriyaki tofu, shrimp, salmon and chicken are soo flavorful and saucy. Comes with a balance of vegetables to pair off. Sushi: a huge selections of sushi, rolls and hand rolls to choose from but they do NOT offer sashimi. The AYCE fill in paper comes with a menu with description and picture. Two restroom located in the back of the store. Super clean and space. Lunch menu $13.95 Dinner menu $19.95 I would suggest requesting for a dinner menu during lunch hours. Lunch hours consist of less people than dinner, reducing your wait time by half. As well as the speed of receiving your food. The lunch menu is half of what they offer on the dinner menu.

We received a menu from this place in my mailbox.  My wife wanted to pay a visit after reading the menu since she loves sushi.  Once I entered, I noticed how clean and well-lit this place was.  This is in contrast to a neighborhood full of restaurants that are on the dirty and unattractive side.  The walls, decor, and furniture were all very stylish and worked together well.  I ordered the vegetable teriyaki dish.  It came with a salad that had a delicious ginger-carrot dressing on it.  We had age tofu as an appetizer.  It's crunchy outer-shell combined with a soft tofu inside was an interesting flavor contrast.  The vegetable teriyaki had a light delicious sauce and was a nice-sized portion.  I was very impressed with the owner who personally came to my table to apologize that they overcooked my dish without my knowledge and asked me to please be patient while they cook a new order for me.  Now that's service!  My wife's sushi order came beautifully presented decorated with a little tree.  She enjoyed her dish.  Our meal was capped off with an offering of watermelon slices which was yet another detail that made this place stand out among other sushi establishments.  We ordered green tea ice cream for dessert.  It was presented with a dallop of whipped cream and drizzled with chocolate syrup.  It was very tasty without being too sweet.  The workers in this restaurant were very pleasant.  Overall, this place was a great experience for my family.
